{"id": 5234, "title": "Ticket #5234: condor_vacate ignores other arguments when -constraint is passed.", "description": "<blockquote>\n<pre>    sudo condor_vacate mem1.chtc.wisc.edu -constraint 'RemoteOwner =!= \"bchen79@chtc.wisc.edu\" &amp;&amp; RemoteOwner =!= \"fmoya@chtc.wisc.edu\"'\n</pre>\n\n<p>The above began vacating the entire pool. (most likely because the explicit <code>-constaint</code> overrode the implied constraint of the machine name.)\n\n</p><p>Investigation of the code indicates that all condor_tool commands ignore most other arguments when passed -constraint. (it hits the same code path as passing -all).   It should exit when an error message when -constraint is passed along with other arguments that would be ignored.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Aug-27 12:43</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/ac769236bb2911137066dd557561bab6733cd2bf\">[45732]</a></span>: copy edited versions of 8.2.10 version history items into the 8.3.8 version history: <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5219\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5219'); return false;\" title=\"Memory leak in ClassAd function split()\">#5219</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5234\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5234'); return false;\" title=\"condor_vacate ignores other arguments when -constraint is passed.\">#5234</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5236\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_pop